// soak jul09c fuzz 000003: a per-slot clone of an analysis-pred tree re-inits
// queuefn with resolved=None (the pred's swallowed typecheck0 died upstream at a
// pre-existing map-source union mismatch, so the inner callsite never computed
// resolved_ftype). queuefn then emitted a QueueFnErr VALUE where its static type
// promises a function, and the caller CallSite's downcast panicked — killing the
// runtime. Fixed by deriving the wrapper type from the runtime f value's own
// LambdaDef when resolved never arrived (queuefn.rs).
array::map([(i64:0, i64:1), ("y", i64:2)], |(s, n)| "[s][s][try (i64:0 /? i64:0)? catch(e) => select e.0.error {`ArithError(s) => {let depth = i64:0; let qf = queuefn(#count: &depth, #trigger: never(), |x: i64| -> i64 x * i64:10); qf(i64:1); qf(i64:2); qf(i64:3); array::group(depth, |n, _| n == i64:3)}}]")
